    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2017-09-08</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2018-04-24T20:26:50Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><b>Labor, Human, and Civil Rights Trade Policy Act</b></p> <p>This bill amends the Bipartisan Congressional Trade Priorities and Accountability Act of 2015 to require trade agreement implementing bills to: (1) achieve the negotiating objectives of adherence by parties to internationally recognized core labor standards; and (2) ensure that parties demonstrate respect for internationally recognized human rights, as indicated through assessments over a period of at least 10 years. For purposes of the meaning of core labor standards, the bill expands the definition of employment discrimination.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
